'''Ottavio Torricelli''', in Latin ''Octavius Turricellius'' (...-17th century) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Philosophy|philosopher]]. He was an [[Emilia-Romagna|Emilian]] patrician and his work was related to [[Claudio Rangoni (bishop of Reggio Emilia)|Claudio Rangoni]].

